headline: Stocks to Watch Friday: JPMorgan, Wells Fargo, BlackRock, Novartis
summary: ? JP Morgan (JPM): Shares in the bank rallied Friday morning after it posted better-than-expected quarterly earnings. Chief Executive Jamie Dimon said the "economy is facing considerable turbulence." Wells Fargo (WFC) also posted above-forecast net income, but shares fell.

headline: Surprising new inflation data sends MicroStrategy, Coinbase stock soaring
summary: The Producer Price Index (PPI) in March came lower than expected. MicroStrategy and most other crypto stocks lied in the green zone in pre-market hours.
